This was great   funny too.  Always been a big fan of Bill s.  Although I 
never got to see him perform live  I did have an unexpected encounter with 
him once.  It was 1986   I was 14 yrs old  living in Oklahoma City   
waiting at the airport gate  back when family could go all the way up to 
the gate  for my Aunt from Montana to arrive to help out with my sick 
mother. There were several security guys standing around  dressed in suits  
with walkie talkies.  We thought maybe they were secret service   some big 
politician was on board.  But wouldn t you know it  Bill Cosby himself came 
walking off the plane   walked right by me.  I mean he was so close  his 
pant leg actually brushed by my shirt   LoL  Needless to say  I was 
flabergasted cuz I was not only a fan  had all his comedy albums  but the 
Cosby show was also HUGE at the time.  I would ve killed to get his 
autograph but he looked like he was in a hurry.  Besides  I don t think I 
coulda got two words out anyway.  I was a shy kid   my jaw was still on the 
floor even after he was way down the hall.  But it was still awesome   a 
brush with fame I won t soon forget.  Btw  I found out later on that he was 
making a commencement speech at some college there.
